The paper deals with the problem of nearest neighbor search, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper presents a new data structure for approximate $k$-flat nearest neighbor search, which is a variant of the nearest neighbor search problem. The paper uses techniques from computational geometry, machine learning, and information theory. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, since the paper deals with applications in computer vision (as mentioned in the introduction), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper uses techniques from information theory (as mentioned in the abstract), cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible sub-category.
